AristaBgp4V2IdentifierTC.name: AristaBgp4V2IdentifierTC
AristaBgp4V2IdentifierTC.description: The representation of a BGP Identifier. BGP Identifiers are presented in the received network byte order. The BGP Identifier is displayed as if it is an IP address, even if it would be an illegal one.

AristaBgp4V2AddressFamilyIdentifierTC.name: AristaBgp4V2AddressFamilyIdentifierTC
AristaBgp4V2AddressFamilyIdentifierTC.description: The representation of a BGP AFI. The value of this object should be restricted to be between the values of 0 and 65535.

AristaBgp4V2SubsequentAddressFamilyIdent.name: AristaBgp4V2SubsequentAddressFamilyIdentifierTC
AristaBgp4V2SubsequentAddressFamilyIdent.description: The representation of a BGP SAFI
AristaBgp4V2SubsequentAddressFamilyIdent.reference: RFC 4760, Section 3. The value of this object should be restricted to be between the values of 0 and 255.
